"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-usa-olympic-sailing-team-roster-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"For a second consecutive Olympics, the U.S. qualified for nine of the 10 sailing events and will send 13 total sailors to compete at the Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sarah Newberry Moore and David Liebenberg clinched the last spots on the U.S. sailing team for Paris on Thursday, filling the mixed-gender multihull (Nacra 17) boat to go to their first Games.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 145, \"end\": 150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"score\": 0.9748209364001331, \"rank\": 0.012978707470779467, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\"}, {\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\", \"score\": 0.9777507653696275, \"rank\": 0.022752114523421543, \"text\": \"Newberry\", \"types\": [\"Q7075\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newberry_Library\"}, {\"begin\": 160, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9999930219894569, \"rank\": 5.339839018737871e-06, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999873145954, \"rank\": 1.2685328143183064e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team is led by its youngest female member, Daniela Moroz, who was the first American sailor to qualify for Paris last August.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"score\": 0.9978460065565581, \"rank\": 0.002157579469363705, \"text\": \"Daniela\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\"}, {\"begin\": 419, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999898830599425, \"rank\": 7.141127227542041e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 450, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999873145954, \"rank\": 1.2685328143183064e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moroz, 23, is a six-time world champion in formula kite, the fastest Olympic sailing event (speeds eclipse 40 miles per hour) and one that makes its Olympic debut this summer.\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stu McNay, 42, is the oldest member of the team and headed to his fifth Olympics, tying the record for a U.S. sailor.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_for_Tomorrow\", \"score\": 0.9496289426475928, \"rank\": 0.05304288344157842, \"text\": \"Stu\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_for_Tomorrow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_for_Tomorrow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic sailing competition is scheduled in Marseille from July 28 through Aug. 8.\"